PART II USER INSTRUCTIONS (to users) \
\
MCIT 591 Investment Planning Statement (IPS) Planner ( \'93 the Program\'94 )  is \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 to help the user understand the investment return and risk objectives, as well as providing recommended asset allocation and corresponding portfolio return and risks based on the user\'92s risk tolerance.\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0  During the use of the Program, the user is \
\
The users can click on the following buttons throughout the program. \
\'93Start\'94 to go back to the first panel of the Program\
\'93Next\'94 to go to the next panel \
\'93Previous\'94 to go to the previous panel \
\'93Exit\'94 to end the program during any step\
\
\
Step 1: the users read and accept the terms and agreements in order to use the Program. \
\
Step 2: there users enter the personal investment information including the user name, user occupation, desired investment horizon, user annual income, user current asset, user annual income and expense, and the desired investment target amount at the end of the investment horizon. \
\
Step 3: the users answer six questions. These questions determine the users\'92 overall investment risk tolerance, the willingness and ability to tolerate investment risks. Where there are inconsistency between the willingness and ability, the Program will generate an alert. In reality, many investors do not have consistent , which will not stop the user\
\
Step 4: the Program displays a screen with the analysis of the user\'92s risk tolerance profile, including the overall risk score, willingness and ability to tolerate investment risks. \
\
Step 5: the Program displays a screen with the analysis of the user\'92s desired return objective. If the objective is challenging to achieve, the Programs will generate an alert. \
\
Step 6: the Program displays a screen with the recommended portfolio allocation to each class based on the user\'92s risk score. The Program also shows the portfolio return and standard deviation based on the user\'92s risk profile. Please note that the recommended portfolio return and standard deviation may be different from the user\'92s desired return and standard deviation. However, the recommended portfolio return is realistic. \
\
Step 7: the user can end the program by clicking on \'93Exit\'94 or \'93Next\'94 in the last panel. \
